HEADWORD: Archery
<hw>Arch"er*y</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>archerie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The use of the bow and
arrows in battle, hunting, etc.; the art, practice, or skill of shooting
with a bow and arrows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Archers, or bowmen, collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let all our <qex>archery</qex> fall off⟦br⟧
In wings of shot a-both sides of the van.</q> <rj><qau>Webster
(1607).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arches</ent>⟦br⟧
